  "body": "<!---\r\nThanks for creating an Pull Request 💖!\r\n\r\nPlease read the following before submitting:\r\n- PRs that adds new external dependencies might take a while to review.\r\n- Keep your PR as small as possible.\r\n- Limit your PR to one type (docs, feature, refactoring, ci, or bugfix)\r\n-->\r\n\r\nCloses # <!-- Github issue # here -->\r\n\r\n## 📝 Description\r\n\r\n> Add a brief description\r\n\r\nBoth the `nested-menu.ts` example and website documentation suggests that `setChild` and `setParent` only need to be set once in their code samples, but the `service` is a transient object that contains new data on every render. By limiting the types to more precise `ChildMenuService` and `ParentMenuService` it's clearer that the used data is stable, and simultaneously we ensure that the machine or connect functions don't break the expectations.\r\n\r\n## ⛳️ Current behavior (updates)\r\n\r\n> Please describe the current behavior that you are modifying\r\n\r\nFrom `website/data/snippets/solid/menu/nested-menu.mdx`:\r\n```ts\r\nonMount(() => {\r\n  setTimeout(() => {\r\n    fileMenu().setChild(shareService)\r\n    shareMenu().setParent(fileService)\r\n  })\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n## 🚀 New behavior\r\n\r\n> Please describe the behavior or changes this PR adds\r\n\r\n## 💣 Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\n\r\n<!-- If Yes, please describe the impact and migration path for existing users. -->\r\n\r\n## 📝 Additional Information\r\n",
